From: Qianfeng Rong <rongqianfeng@vivo.com>
Date: Mon, 4 Aug 2025 20:27:30 +0800
Subject: bpf: Remove redundant __GFP_NOWARN
Patch-mainline: v6.18-rc1
Git-commit: 3e2b799008a78c21c648328bed9f566335f0394e
References: jsc#PED-14653

Commit 16f5dfbc851b ("gfp: include __GFP_NOWARN in GFP_NOWAIT")
made GFP_NOWAIT implicitly include __GFP_NOWARN.

Therefore, explicit __GFP_NOWARN combined with GFP_NOWAIT
(e.g., `GFP_NOWAIT | __GFP_NOWARN`) is now redundant. Let's clean
up these redundant flags across subsystems.

No functional changes.

Signed-off-by: Qianfeng Rong <rongqianfeng@vivo.com>
Signed-off-by: Andrii Nakryiko <andrii@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Jiri Olsa <jolsa@kernel.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/bpf/20250804122731.460158-1-rongqianfeng@vivo.com
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 kernel/bpf/devmap.c        |    2 +-
 kernel/bpf/local_storage.c |    2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/kernel/bpf/devmap.c
+++ b/kernel/bpf/devmap.c
@@ -865,7 +865,7 @@ static struct bpf_dtab_netdev *__dev_map
 	struct bpf_dtab_netdev *dev;
 
 	dev = bpf_map_kmalloc_node(&dtab->map, sizeof(*dev),
-				   GFP_NOWAIT | __GFP_NOWARN,
+				   GFP_NOWAIT,
 				   dtab->map.numa_node);
 	if (!dev)
 		return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
--- a/kernel/bpf/local_storage.c
+++ b/kernel/bpf/local_storage.c
@@ -165,7 +165,7 @@ static long cgroup_storage_update_elem(s
 	}
 
 	new = bpf_map_kmalloc_node(map, struct_size(new, data, map->value_size),
-				   __GFP_ZERO | GFP_NOWAIT | __GFP_NOWARN,
+				   __GFP_ZERO | GFP_NOWAIT,
 				   map->numa_node);
 	if (!new)
 		return -ENOMEM;
